from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

target_explained_variance_ratio = 0.95

pca = PCA(n_components=numerical_df_clean_standardized.shape[1])

pca.fit(numerical_df_clean_standardized)

# Calculate the cumulative explained variance ratio
cumulative_explained_variance_ratio = np.cumsum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)

# Determine the number of components needed to achieve the target explained variance
num_components_for_target_ratio = np.argmax(cumulative_explained_variance_ratio >= target_explained_variance_ratio) + 1

# Apply PCA with the determined number of components
pca = PCA(n_components=num_components_for_target_ratio)
X_pca = pca.fit_transform(numerical_df_clean_standardized)

print(f"Number of components for {target_explained_variance_ratio * 100:.2f}% explained variance: {num_components_for_target_ratio}")
print(f"Total explained variance with {num_components_for_target_ratio} components: {cumulative_explained_variance_ratio[num_components_for_target_ratio - 1]:.4f}")

# Now, X_pca contains your data transformed into the reduced feature space
